    <item>
      <title>12.24 The Owner of the Plaque</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-24-the-owner-of-the-plaque/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-24-the-owner-of-the-plaque/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 13 Dec 2023 10:23:36 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.24 The Owner of the&amp;nbsp;Plaque&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: Initially, I translated 大将軍 as Commander-in-Chief back in chapter 3, but it&amp;#8217;s now General-in-Chief. Commander-in-Chief is now the translation for 大司馬 (which I believe is translated as Grand Marshal in the official translation, which I&amp;#8217;d already used for Papa dearest, alas.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-23-the-identity-of-the-wet-nurse/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems the military was divided into three factions.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The first was the top brass of the military, General-in-chief Lu. Originally appointed as the empress dowager’s guard, now promoted. Commonly known as the Empress Dowager Faction.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Second was the supporters of Gyoku’en who had recently emerged. Gyoku’en was a civil official, but he gathered country-bred people who were far from promotion. He was uncertain to become the leader, but it was said that he gathered people who weren’t satisfied with their current treatment even if they’re from the named clans. As it was Gyoku’en, they are also known as the Empress Faction.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Third was said to be commanded by the weirdo tactician, but would that be misleading? Known to be neutral, but no one knew of the weirdo tactician’s intentions. However, he was good at dragging out obscure talented individuals, so you could even say that he gathered loyal people.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was what Mamei had told Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“His imperial majesty has conferred the Gyoku character to the empress’ clan. In response, Commander-in-Chief Lu has been promoted to General-in-Chief.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is there a meaning to that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He was already the highest ranking person in the military.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The move to bring out an unused post from the past, is to inform others that the General-in-chief will remain in the highest position. The General-in-Chief isn’t from a named clan, and there probably won’t be any more new clans after Gyoku for a while after.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems a highborn person like the emperor had to be careful about his retainers.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“One question. Is he related to Vice Minister Lu from the Ministry of Rites?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think they’re too distantly related; it&amp;#8217;d be difficult to call them relatives. Like a second cousin of a second cousin.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Almost strangers, then.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She should take it that he has no connection with Yao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why did you purposely ask such a question?” Mamei’s raptor eyes smiled.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well, all you’ve been telling me are topics that wear me out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“They’re things you need to hear. The clans Maomao-san interacted with at this conference are U, Shin and Ma, who have a long history even among the named clans. If I must say, they are of the Empress Dowager’s Faction. Conversely, the families not titled with the characters of the zodiac are new. Most of these are families younger than the Ra clan.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mamei looked out the carriage. The wheels rattled.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Recently, hot blooded people have been making a great fuss. Maomao-san’s section must be dealing with a lot of injured people, so please take care.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tell me that earlier.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought while she looked outside.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When they arrived at Jinshi’s palace, Taomei was there, as Mamei predicted.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Taomei politely bowed her head at Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How was the conference?” She checked with her daughter with an elegant expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Without a hitch.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They may be mother and daughter, but today they were in work mode.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well then, leave the rest to me, and return to inform the family.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood.” Mamei withdrew in haste.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, the Moon Prince is waiting, please head in.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi’s room was fragrant as always. The nice and cold air was probably because there was ice placed in the corner of the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;How luxurious.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She thought, and Jinshi beckoned at her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Take a seat,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Certainly.” Maomao sat down on a chair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Here you are.” Suiren appeared and set a glass cup in front of Maomao. It contained cold tea.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you very much.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;How should I interact with Suiren?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought for a moment, but decided to treat her as she normally did. It was better to not think too deeply about complicated human relationships.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t that she was hiding what Mamei had told her without a care. It was just that she wasn’t explaining since she wasn’t asked about it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve found out about the jade plaque you asked me to look into before,” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Whose is it?” Maomao held her breath.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“His real name hadn’t been left behind. However, I believe it belonged to an imperial who had been known as Kada.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Kada…” It was a name Maomao had heard before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It seems to be a famous name among the court physicians.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s the name of a legendary doctor.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right. However, the name is known among the imperials for a different meaning. I heard he was a former imperial who had been executed for committing a taboo in the past.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What taboo?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That man was both an imperial and a court physician. He possessed outstanding skill to the point of being called the name of a legendary doctor. This man, in a pursuit for new skills, had dissected, of all people, the imperial prince that was most favoured by the emperor at the time.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao gulped.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Despite being an imperial as well, he wasn’t pardoned and his name was crossed out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You are telling me that it’s that person’s plaque?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao shut her eyes tightly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a good enough reason to deface the jade plaque. The court physicians dissected in secrecy. Furthermore, they only did it to criminals since people believed that damage to the body will prevent reincarnation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Once you’re dead, you’re just meat.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The emperor at the time probably wasn’t pragmatic enough to think that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The reason that person’s jade plaque is here would mean that Kada had passed it onto someone while he was alive.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;I guess so.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And the person he would have given it to would be…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The woman who gave birth to his child.” Maomao scratched her head.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She couldn’t believe that Joka was truly and genuinely descended from the imperial family.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Kada is an imperial from several generations ago. I doubt his imperial majesty would punish that person’s descendants now.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That, I believe.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“However, the problem is that there are people who have attempted to get their hands on that plaque.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Joka had asked Maomao for advice after someone tried to steal it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What would happen if they get their hands on a plaque that is already defaced and split right into two?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“They can use it as justification,” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not a drama.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Countries have fallen into ruin, or flourished due to laughable reasons like a drama.” Jinshi had a serious look in his eyes. “The empress dowager’s lover had attempted to invigorate the nation, a eunuch had attempted to found a country–those things have happened.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By saying attempted, you mean that they ended in rebellion.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“On rare occasions they do succeed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“History is unpleasant.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi had a distant stare. “Is it fine if I hold onto the jade plaque?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Under such circumstances, there’s nothing I can do about it. However, may I explain the situation to the owner of the plaque?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was the tool of Joka’s trade. She would need to explain even if she had passed it over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It depends on the person’s gender.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Female.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’ll need to make sure she doesn’t leak it out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;I’ll let her know.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Would Joka think that she shouldn’t have asked Maomao for the favour if that was how it was going to turn out? She would be stealing away her sales lure.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If she keeps her promise, I’ll guarantee her safety.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you very much.” Maomao sighed and picked up the glass cup. Water dripped down the glass from condensation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Bitterness at first, then sweetness filled her mouth. It wasn’t the half-fermented tea she always drank, but completely dried tea leaves.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Could someone be planning a rebellion or something?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We are limited to cutting potential cases at the bud for now.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, you’ll have to find where the other half of the plaque is, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have other things to do so I can’t organise a search solely for that.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi picked up a mooncake. Maomao kept glancing at Suiren to see if there were crackers, but she didn’t bring any out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By the way, I heard you went to the Named Meeting. How was it?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The weirdo was there, so use your judgement please.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Got it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I believe a few things happened, but I’m sure Jinshi-sama would have already received a report from an excellent spy. It’s not like I would say everything that there is to be said.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She could talk about the duel between the man from the Shin clan who had been wooing Yao and Rahan’s older brother. However, she had second thoughts about talking about the matter between the Shin and U.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi made a look of desolation, but Maomao also had her position to consider.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How have you been lately, Jinshi-sama? Your complexion has improved a little compared to how it was in the western capital.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve been pulling fewer all-nighters.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“They’re not foisting tasks on you anymore?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I have more capable subordinates,” Jinshi said, but he had a faraway look in his eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is your subordinate capable but problematic?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If I tell you it’s Hulang, would you understand?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Right.” Maomao understood. “Is it fine to leave him so close to you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll manage if I regard him as a Rahan with a slightly different disposition.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wow, what a superbly unpleasant subordinate.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He could do his work, but he would give improper looks to his boss.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He’s quite capable as an aide. Once in a while, it looks like he has grasped the weakness of a civil official from another department.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He truly is a Rahan with a different disposition.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan would deny it, but that had nothing to do with Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Speaking of what’s weighing on my mind, there’s the jade plaque from just then, but there’s also the factions in the military.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It&amp;#8217;s been the hot topic lately.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao should be careful too. The weirdo tactician’s influence has weakened somewhat this year.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have no intention of hiding behind that old man’s influence.” Maomao looked utterly displeased.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi reached out to Maomao. His hand stopped just before touching her hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you not touch me?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I want to. Not just that, I want to hold you. I want to squeeze you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re not doing it, huh,” Maomao said teasingly. Before, he would willfully touch despite how many times she told him not to.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Squeezing won’t be the end of it. I’ll bite and lick you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I shuddered just now.” Maomao narrowed her eyes just a smidge.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How absurdly rude.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi didn’t get angry. He merely looked at Maomao enviously.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, I’ll have to be rude.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Going back already?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I should head back before it gets dark. I have work tomorrow you see.” Maomao looked outside. The sun had yet to set.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well then, excuse me.” Maomao drank all the tea, and moved her wet fingers towards Jinshi. Then she pressed down on his wrist and slid down from the back of his hands to his middle finger.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"&gt;&lt;img width="726" height="1023" src="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/screenshot_20231213_212645.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4340" sizes="(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi made an indescribable expression, so Maomao felt like she had won for no reason.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Until next time.” She slowly bowed her head and left Jinshi’s palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: And that&amp;#8217;s the end of the Kada arc. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;Well, I did say that I&amp;#8217;m only here for arc 12, but I did arc 11 as well, so I might as well continue, right? &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/13-01-the-summons/"&gt;Next chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-24-the-owner-of-the-plaque/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4334-686908fbd6ce7' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250705#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4334&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4334-686908fbd6ce7' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4334-686908fbd6ce7' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-24-the-owner-of-the-plaque/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
